    <h1>3D Missile Command</h1>
    <a href="https://github.com/hccoffin/3D-Missile-Command">Github Repo</a>
    <p>
        Players are in a 3D world where they fire at incoming missiles coming
        towards Earth from all directions. We developed a method for users to
        click in 3D through the rotation of the cameraâ€™s parallel plane. The
        game also includes a minimap radar for visualization of the virtual
        world. Based on the classic 80's Atari game Missile Command.
    </p>
    <p>
        Built with Python, VPython
    </p>
    <p>
        Hack 112 November 2016 Project created with Yuyi Shen, Ben Soudry, and
        Jerry Yu.
    </p>
    <p>
        Awarded Grand Prize Second Place
    </p>
